{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-recipe-page-js","path":"/rice-waffles/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Chez Nosredna"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"047d6de2-5b7a-519f-a3b3-18d519b543ce","excerpt":"If you make some extra rice for dinner the night before, then this comes together quickly. If you didn’t, add in some extra prep time for making the rice. If…","html":"<p>If you make some extra rice for dinner the night before, then this comes together quickly. If you didn’t, add in some extra prep time for making the rice.</p>\n<p>If the rice is hot, be careful not to add the eggs directly to the hot rice, or you risk cooking the eggs prematurely (in the mixing bowl).</p>\n<p>A belgian waffle iron works fine, but we prefer the texture that results from using a more traditional waffle iron (the thinner waffles have more surface area).</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Norwegian Rice Waffles","date":"December 12, 2020","description":"Carolyn Matthews' family recipe","prep":"10 mins","cook":"20 mins","servings":"3-4","tags":["Breakfast","Dessert","Vegan(ish)"],"tools":[{"name":"waffle iron","note":null}],"ingredients":[{"ingredient":"3 cups cooked rice (1 cup dry)","note":"experiment with different kinds of rice!"},{"ingredient":"⅓ cup sugar","note":"original calls for ½ cup; reducing the sugar makes the waffles less crispy"},{"ingredient":"1¼ cup flour","note":null},{"ingredient":"¼ cup vegetable oil","note":"original calls for half a stick of butter or margarine"},{"ingredient":"1 cup milk","note":"coconut milk is a delicious substitute"},{"ingredient":"½ tsp ground cardamom","note":"original calls for 12 seeds (seeds, not pods)"},{"ingredient":"3 eggs","note":"substituting flax eggs and/or chia seeds works great"}],"sauce":null,"suggestions":[{"ingredient":"butter","note":null},{"ingredient":"maple syrup","note":null},{"ingredient":"honey","note":null},{"ingredient":"jam or compote","note":null}],"full_img":{"publicURL":"/static/full-b7603230b7